Prerequisites :
- FFmpeg : https://www.ffmpeg.org/
- Vapoursynth R27+ : http://www.vapoursynth.com/
- Vapoursynth's FFMS2 plugin : https://github.com/FFMS/ffms2/releases
- Vapoursynth's HAvsFunc plugin : http://forum.doom9.org/showthread.php?t=166582
- Vapoursynth's SceneChange plugin : http://forum.doom9.org/showthread.php?t=166769
- Vapoursynth's fmtconv plugin : http://forum.doom9.org/showthread.php?t=166504
- (Recommended) Vapoursynth Editor : http://forum.doom9.org/showthread.php?t=170965
- (Optional) Vapoursynth's nnedi3_rpow2 plugin : http://forum.doom9.org/showthread.php?t=172652
- (Very optional) Vapoursynth's Waifu2x-w2xc plugin : https://github.com/HomeOfVapourSynthEvolution/VapourSynth-Waifu2x-w2xc/

Unix Prerequisites :
- Vapoursynth's GenericFilters plugin : https://github.com/myrsloik/GenericFilters
- Tesseract (version 3.03+ recommended) and its English dictionnary : https://github.com/tesseract-ocr/tesseract
- Links : http://links.twibright.com/
- Simple X Image Viewer : https://github.com/muennich/sxiv
- xdotool (Linux only) : http://www.semicomplete.com/projects/xdotool/
- GNU Parallel (version 20131122+ recommended)Â : http://www.gnu.org/software/parallel/

Windows Prerequisites :
- Tesseract and its English dictionnary : https://code.google.com/p/tesseract-ocr/downloads/detail?name=tesseract-ocr-setup-3.02.02.exe
- Cygwin : https://www.cygwin.com/
- Packages to activate during Cygwin installation :
	gnupg
	wget
	perl
	bc
	links
- Install GNU Parallel, from Cygwin terminal :
	wget -O - pi.dk/3 | bash
	mv ~/bin/parallel /usr/local/bin/
- Cygwin terminal usage :
	https://help.ubuntu.com/community/UsingTheTerminal
	C drive path is "/cygdrive/c".
	Scripts have to be used within Cygwin terminal.


Installation script for all the prerequisites on Debian Jessie and LMDE Betsy :
	sh YoloDebInstallation.sh eng-only

Vapoursynth PPA for Ubuntu and Linux Mint (not tested) :
	https://launchpad.net/~djcj/+archive/ubuntu/vapoursynth


The OCR procedure consists of two steps :
First, you'll have to filter the video with Vapoursynth. Don't forget to edit the first lines in YoloCR.vpy according to your source file.
vspipe -y YoloCR.vpy - | ffmpeg -i - -c:v mpeg4 -qscale:v 3 -y Filtered_Video.mp4
You now have an OCR-isable video and scenechange informations.
Then you can OCR the video.
./YoloCR.sh Filtered_Video.mp4
Now it's Checking time :D

Help for determining the parameters :
First, open YoloResize in Vapoursynth Editor.
	FichierSource is the path of the video to OCR. Don't forget the apostrophes.
	DimensionCropbox allows you to limit the OCR zone.
	HauteurCropBox allows you to define the height of the Cropbox's bottom border.
Note that theses two parameters have to be adjusted before upscale.
	You can then change Supersampling parameter to -1 and verify that your subtitles aren't eated by the white borderline.
Now open YoloSeuil in the editor.
	Define FichierSource, DimensionCropBox and HauteurCropBox like you did previously.
	Choose the fitting ModeS. 'L' if you want to define a white or black threshold, succesively 'R', 'G' and 'B' otherwise.
	Adjust the Seuil (Threshold).
		Inline threshold have to be as high as possible, but subtitles must remain completely visible.
		Outline threshold have to be as low as possible, but outline must remain fully black.


